<#--F2.2 What are the most important harms and benefits to consider for the groups as at risk of disadvantages in F1? -->
<div>
The potential harms to customers are:
<ul>
<li>it will be more difficult for customers to apply for credit products successfully, who have a loan application declined that go on their financial record;</li>
<li>they may default on a loan that they would have otherwise not acquired.</li>
</ul>
The potential benefits to customers are:
<ul>
<li>they can learn more about loan products and meet their unfulfilled needs;</li>
<li>the marketing call provides them with the opportunity to apply for credit products without waiting in a queue at a branch or on the phone.</li>
</ul>
</div>

